  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2000-05-16", 
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow as a deduction, subject to limitations, an amount equal to the sum of the amount paid during the taxable year for: (1) insurance which constitutes medical care for the taxpayer and the taxpayer's spouse and dependents; plus (2) unreimbursed prescription drug expenses paid by the taxpayer for the taxpayer and the taxpayer's spouse and dependents."
